Captured Peruvian drug trafficker Demetrio Chavez  Penaherrara has accused high-ranking Peruvian military leaders of helping his  drug operations, according to press reports Sunday.
Chavez accused Eduardo Bellido Mora, a general currently serving as the  military attache in Israel and Major Carlos Rodriguez Cateriano, whose current  assignment was not identified.
Chavez alleged the two were among military officers who took payoffs for  drug shipments. He made his statements during an interview with members of a  government panel.
He was captured in Colombia in January.
